The paper deals with algorithms for computing longest common extension queries and runs in strings, which are fundamental problems in string algorithms. The main tools used in the paper are difference covers and the disjoint-sets data structure, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and information-theoretic techniques, which suggest that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper deals with time complexity analysis, which is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves techniques from formal languages, which suggest that it could belong to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper involves information-theoretic techniques, which suggest that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
